  "prompt": "Why was the wax museum in Philadelphia built?",
  "response": "The wax museum in Philadelphia, known as the Philadelphia Wax Museum, was built to provide an engaging and educational experience for visitors by showcasing life-like wax figures of historical figures, celebrities, and notable individuals. Wax museums serve as a means to preserve cultural history and allow people to connect with important moments and figures from the past in an interactive way. The Philadelphia Wax Museum specifically aimed to celebrate the city's rich history and its role in American culture, offering a unique attraction for both locals and tourists. It provided an opportunity for people to learn about history through an artistic and entertaining medium.",
